
Installation
------------

Prerequisites:

 - LibXML (http://xmlsoft.org/downloads.html)
 - Python 2.5 or newer (www.python.org)
 - Twisted framework (http://twistedmatrix.com) - Twisted Core, Twisted Web and Twisted Web 2
 - python-lxml (http://codespeak.net/lxml)
 - python-application
 - python-xml

 To enable TLS support, you need:
 - GnuTLS library (http://www.gnu.org/software/gnutls)
 - python-gnutls (http://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-gnutls)

The software has been tested on debian unstable using the following versions:

 - libxml2: 2.6.32.dfsg-2
 - python: 2.5.2-1
 - python-application: 1.0.9-4
 - python-gnutls: 1.1.5-2
 - python-lxml: 2.0.5-1
 - python-sqlobject: 0.10.1-1
 - python-twisted-core: 8.0.1-1
 - python-twisted-web: 8.0.0-1
 - python-twisted-web2: 8.0.1-1
 - python-zopeinterface: 3.3.1-6


Testing
-------

There's a test suite you can ran against a freshly installed server. It is
located in xcap/test directory (look at /usr/lib/python2.5/site-packages/xcap/test
if you have installed the server from debian package).
To run the whole test suite run something like this:

  python test.py --xcap-root https://xcap.example.com/xcap-root --username alice@example.com --password 123

NOTE: This will result in destruction of xcap documents belonging to user alice@example.com.
Replacing 'test.py' with 'test_something.py' will only run tests defined in test_something.py.
